ns might occur. It's an intricate setup!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining error handling**\\n\\nI need to make sure I’m following the rule to catch errors, verify them, and rethrow if necessary. I wonder if swallowing these errors is permitted. The framework indicates catching errors might be crucial, especially since Native Image failures can arise. I think I should account for `InvocationTargetException`, which could happen when using reflection to inject constructors. Specifically, I need to consider what happens if the transformation leads to unsupported features. It’s all a bit tricky!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_zZxF7m8e2VViKaUwg0lNMKbI|fc_080e35c9554e80fc016a26bd117a3c8196a79424f6af82625e", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/AddDelegateTransformerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage cglib.cglib_nodep;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.asm.ClassWriter;\nimport net.sf.cglib.asm.MethodVisitor;\nimport net.sf.cglib.asm.Opcodes;\nimport net.sf.cglib.transform.ClassTransformer;\nimport net.sf.cglib.transform.TransformingClassLoader;\nimport net.sf.cglib.transform.impl.AddDelegateTransformer;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class AddDelegateTransformerTest {\n    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS_NAME = \"cglib.cglib_nodep.AddDelegateTransformerGenerated\";\n    private static final String GENERATED_INTERNAL_NAME = \"cglib/cglib_nodep/AddDelegateTransformerGenerated\";\n\n    @Test\n    void addsInterfaceMethodsBackedByDelegateImplementation() throws Exception {\n        TransformingClassLoader loader = new TransformingClassLoader(\n                new GeneratedClassPathLoader(),\n                GENERATED_CLASS_NAME::equals,\n                AddDelegateTransformerTest::newDelegateTransformer);\n\n        try {\n            Class<?> transformed = loader.loadClass(GENERATED_CLASS_NAME);\n            Object instance = transformed.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance();\n            DynamicDelegate delegate = DynamicDelegate.class.cast(instance);\n\n            assertThat(transformed.getInterfaces()).contains(DynamicDelegate.class);\n            assertThat(delegate.describe(\"subject\")).isEqualTo(\"delegate:subject\");\n            assertThat(delegate.getTarget()).isSameAs(instance);\n        } catch (InvocationTargetException exception) {\n            if (findUnsupportedFeatureError(exception) == null) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n        } catch (RuntimeException exception) {\n            if (findUnsupportedFeatureError(exception) == null) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static ClassTransformer newDelegateTransformer() {\n        return new AddDelegateTransformer(new Class[] {DynamicDelegate.class}, DelegateImpl.class);\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] generatedClassBytecode() {\n        ClassWriter writer = new ClassWriter(0);\n        writer.visit(\n                Opcodes.V1_6,\n                Opcodes.ACC_PUBLIC | Opcodes.ACC_SUPER,\n                GENERATED_INTERNAL_NAME,\n                null,\n                \"java/lang/Object\",\n                null);\n        writeDefaultConstructor(writer);\n        writer.visitEnd();\n        return writer.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static void writeDefaultConstructor(ClassWriter writer) {\n        